5:
It would seem my predictions were 
correct.
9:
A dark World Flipper... 
This must be what connected the East 
and West.
12:
I thought you agreed not to do 
anything rash.
17:
Alk? And Stella too. 
What are you doing here?
21:
We heard you snuck off somewhere 
dangerous on your own, so we came to 
help you.
24:
You don't have to do everything by 
yourself, you know?
27:
But infiltration is most successful in 
minimal—
No, I suppose you're right. I should have 
consulted you earlier.
30:
I planned to ask this later, 
but as you are here now; 
Stella, can you tell what's wrong with 
this World Flipper?
34:
It's out of control.
Suizen, could this be—?
38:
The cause of the two Yamatos' merge, 
if my theories are correct. 
We must be quiet though. 
This forest belongs to—
42:
Me. What business have you in my 
domain, mortals?
50:
Alk, stay back! 
That's not Inaho!
53:
Her aura is unmistakable...
This is the yokai queen of legends—
the golden fox, She of Nine Tails!
55:
You know of me, and yet you dare 
trespass upon my lands?
58:
An army of thousands would 
prove me no challenge. You few 
truly thought you could best me?
70:
Everyone, please calm down. 
She of Nine Tails, we do not wish to 
fight you. 
I came to negotiate with you.
73:
Negotiate? 
And to what do I owe the oh so grand 
honor of civil conversation with a 
diviner?
79:
I would like to ask you to subdue the 
yokai appearing in the East, and take 
them under your command.
84:
When we lifted the elemental seal 
upon them, countless spirits returned 
to their once-home, Yamato of the 
East.
86:
Now, the East is overrun with more 
yokai than we diviners can contain. 
It is only a matter of time before they 
begin invading the West.
88:
I see. 
Pitting the yokai against each other, 
so your diviners can watch from the 
sidelines. Not a bad deal for YOU, is it?
91:
In exchange, the Diviners' Commission 
will ensure your borders are respected 
by humans.
93:
I have heard enough.
I do not see merit in lending you our aid.
94:
To the contrary, we of the West shall 
celebrate your fall when the Eastern 
yokai overthrow your lofty little 
commission.
95:
If I am to crush them either way, 
I may as well get some use out of the 
Easterners first.
98:
Can you crush them alone, though? 
I don't believe you can—at least not 
with this World Flipper demanding so 
much of your power.
101:
What did you do when your daughter 
was captured? When Orochi wreaked 
havoc upon Yamato?
You did nothing.
103:
There was nothing you COULD do, 
because you were here, keeping the 
corrupted World Flipper at bay.
107:
That World Flipper appears to be 
malfunctioning. 
I should be able to stabilize it.
109:
I am indeed suppressing this rift 
between worlds.
You free me from this duty, and in 
exchange I will subdue the yokai of the 
East.
110:
A nice bargain, I suppose, 
but do you truly believe I will uphold 
my end of it? 
Do not presume seals and talismans 
will bind me.
114: I do believe. I know you'll keep your promise.
122:
Do not take me for my foolish daughter.
But yes, my daughter owes you her life. 
I suppose it falls upon me to repay her 
debt.
129:
You may consider your negotiations 
successful. 
The Eastern yokai shall be subdued.
130:
However, this is neither an alliance, 
nor a treaty. The yokai are not your 
friends!
135:
She may, but I do not share such 
sentiments.
138:
...Understood.
Your aid alone is more than cause for 
gratitude. Thank you.
140:
Hah!
Very well, child. I leave the rest to you.
143:
Whew—
I'm glad that ended well. I don't think 
I've ever held my breath so long.
146:
I am sorry to have worried you, Mizuchi. 
And thank you two for coming to check 
on me.
149:
That sure was nerve-wracking! 
It's a good thing she's on our side...
152:
She reminded me of Inaho. 
I could see the family resemblance.
155:
...You were right.
I should have relied on you from the 
start.
157:
Are you ready to stabilize the World 
Flipper?
Mizuchi, you'll help too, right?
160:
I'm ready. 
I need to keep my end of the promise.
164:
With this, we're one step closer to 
restoring order to Yamato!
